SUMMARY:The India Corner: Collection Launch and Remarks by Indian Ambassa
 dor Somnath Ghosh
DESCRIPTION:Deepen your perspective. Access the collection. Meet a vetera
 n practitioner.  The Hamilton Lugar School is officially opening the Indi
 a Corner\, a new specialized lending library and resource hub. This curat
 ed collection offers a deep dive into Indian cultural history\, regional 
 literature\, and social perspectives—providing the essential context ne
 eded to understand one of the world's most significant global powers.  To
  mark the inauguration of this collection\, join us for a briefing with C
 onsul General Somnath Ghosh on the intersection of culture\, history\, an
 d modern diplomacy.The Main Event: Ambassador Somnath GhoshAmbassador Gho
 sh (https://www.cgichicago.gov.in/page/profile/) brings 28 years of diplo
 matic tradecraft to GISB. Before his current assignment in Chicago\, he l
 ed International Cooperation in India's Ministry of Defence\, managing co
 mplex policy and negotiations with the U.S.\, Russia\, and the UK. He off
 ers a unique look at how a deep understanding of history and regional ide
 ntity informs high-stakes global security and the Indo-Pacific strategy. 
  Refreshments provided. Hamilton Lugar School's Office of Policy Engageme
 nt and Strategic Partnerships and Dhar India Studies&#160\;
